programme.title: Tammy and the Teenage T-Rex

programme.title: Halloween: The Curse of Michael Myers

Ed Harris, Miranda Richardson.

programme.title: Mr. Baseball

programme.title: Peace, Love & Misunderstanding

programme.title: The Cold Light of Day
programme.desc: A hotshot stockbroker must save his family after they are kidnapped during a vacation in Spain. In order to do so, he will need to learn dark secrets from his father's past and uncover a government conspiracy.

programme.title: The Conversation
programme.desc: Character study of Harry Caul, an expert wiretapper assigned to surveil a couple in San Francisco. As he learns more about the couple through conversation, Harry wrestles with the notion that his recording could lead to their murder.

programme.title: The Silence of the Lambs
programme.desc: Best Picture winner about an FBI trainee (Best Actress Jodie Foster), who has a knack for analyzing serial killers, and enlists the aid of an imprisoned, cannibalistic sociopath (Best Actor Anthony Hopkins) in tracking a sadistic murderer. An Oscar went to director Jonathan Demme and also Ted Tally won for Best Adapted Screenplay for his script based on the Thomas Harris novel.

Laurie Strode (Curtis) runs a prep school and lives a peaceful life---until her maniac brother returns to crash her son's Halloween party. As a video from the night of the crime surfaces, Mare questions suspects in the case and gives an icy welcome to County Detective Colin Zabel, who's been called in to assist. Later, Mare bumps heads with locals and airs concerns about her grandson Drew in light of her late son's mental health struggles.

programme.title: The Namesake
programme.desc: A Bengali family tries to acclimate to life in the U.S. in this poignant and bittersweet saga of cultures clashing across generations. Their teenage son (Kal Penn) does not embrace their Indian heritage until he visits Calcutta, where he gains an understanding of the importance of his family's past. Indian-born Mira Nair directed from a script by Sooni Taraporevala, who adapted Pulitzer Prize-winner Jhumpa Lahiri's novel. Bollywood superstar Tabu costars as Penn's old-world mother.

programme.title: Fear
programme.desc: What begins as an innocent teenage romance turns to obsession when a charismatic but unbalanced young man sets his sights on a 16-year-old girl.

programme.title: Man Up
programme.desc: In this delightful romantic-comedy Nancy, an unlucky-in-love thirtysomething, meets Jack, a heartbroken divorcé who has recently tried online dating and mistakes Nancy for his arranged blind date when they cross paths. Nancy plays along with the ruse, and the unlikely duo soon find themselves on a whirlwind journey neither of them expected.

programme.title: Up in the Air
programme.desc: This warmhearted dramedy centers on Ryan Bingham, who works for a company that specializes in firing people. Ryan is soon forced to take a newcomer along on a business trip in order to show her firsthand what he does, and he begins to reflect on his lonely life and develops a relationship with fellow frequent flyer Alex Goran.

programme.title: Downhill
programme.desc: Pete and Billie are forced to re-evaluate their marriage after Pete abandons his wife and children during a controlled avalanche at a ski resort in the Alps. The irreconcilable tension between Pete's defensive denials and Billie's trauma plays out throughout the rest of their stay, putting their relationship to the test.

programme.title: In & Out
programme.desc: Kevin Kline's comic turn highlights this winning farce about a straitlaced teacher whose world is shattered when a former student refers to him as gay on TV. The teacher is forced to re-examine his sexuality while fending off his worried bride-to-be (Joan Cusack) and a gay reporter (Tom Selleck). Matt Dillon, Debbie Reynolds, Wilford Brimley Bob Newhart.

programme.title: Stop-Loss
programme.desc: The heroic homecoming of a decorated Army sergeant is cut short when he objects to being ordered back to active duty in Iraq. Ryan Phillippe and Abbie Cornish star in this powerful story. Joseph Gordon-Levitt, Rob Brown, Channing Tatum. Directed by Kimberly Peirce.

programme.title: Midway
programme.desc: In 1942, a few months after the infamous Pearl Harbor attack and a few years before World War II ended, the Japanese forces were once again planning to stage a sudden attack against their opponents this time near the Midway Atoll. Their plan, however, was intercepted, and the American forces arrived at the Pacific Ocean theater just in time to stop them. The battle lasted for three days, and its outcome became a critical turning point in the ongoing war.

programme.title: Autism:The Sequel
programme.desc: This documentary follows five young adults on the spectrum as they navigate their early 20s. Intercut with these present-day interviews is footage of the same youth and their families shot 12 years ago for the Emmy-winning film \"Autism: The Musical.\".

programme.title: Drumline
programme.desc: Energetic drama about a hotshot New York City percussionist who adjusts to the demands of a big-time college marching band while trying to fit in at the prestigious Atlanta university.

programme.title: Emma (?)
programme.desc: A headstrong, high-spirited, and privileged young woman severely overestimates her matchmaking abilities as she meddles in the romantic lives of people in her small and sleepy English town during the 1800s. Hard-won knowledge about the intricacies of love compels her to reconsider her vow never to marry.

programme.title: Pray, Obey, Kill
programme.desc: As the sensational trial begins, key witnesses present their versions of the events leading to January 10. After digging into the nanny's testimony and psychiatric evaluation, Anton and Martin discover that critical evidence may have been withheld. Meanwhile, former members of the sect discuss their leader's vision of God's will.

programme.title: True Grit
programme.desc: In the Coen brothers' stirring remake of the John Wayne classic, an alcoholic U.S. Marshal and an independent-minded 14-year-old girl track down her father's killer with the help of a Texas Ranger. As the three brave dangerous Indian territory, they discover their prey has fallen in with a more-experienced criminal.

programme.title: Safe House
programme.desc: In this pulse-pounding ride, a rookie CIA operative (Ryan Reynolds) goes on the run with a rogue former intelligence officer (Denzel Washington) after a South African safe house comes under attack by heavily armed mercenaries.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: In 1899 London, Amalia True and Penance Adair work to protect their kind from widespread, deepening antipathy, three years after an inexplicable event suddenly equipped them with extraordinary abilities. Meanwhile, police inspector Frank Mundi investigates a string of murders at the hands of a reportedly Touched and highly dangerous serial killer named Maladie. Series premiere.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: The city reels from Maladie's opera debut as Mundi takes a personal stake in tracking her down, and Amalia launches an investigation of her own. Meanwhile, the charitable Lavinia Bidlow seeks to destigmatize the Touched at a society event; Hugo Swann enlists Lavinia's younger brother Augie to help monetize his illicit enterprise; and a deranged doctor conducts a series of experiments.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: Penance creates an amplifier to spread Mary's hope-inspiring song across the city, but first, Mary must find her elusive voice. As danger mounts against her group, Amalia propositions an unlikely ally and sets out to expand the Orphanage's reach. Swann further entangles Augie and Mundi in his business affairs.

programme.title: Lars and the Real Girl
programme.desc: Ryan Gosling gives a bravura performance as a lonely, delusional young man named Lars who surprises his family when he shows up with a new love, a life-size doll he names Bianca and treats like an actual girlfriend. Things take an even quirkier turn when Lars' psychiatrist (Patricia Clarkson) tells his family and friends to humor him and go along with the situation. An offbeat and touching comedy-drama directed by Craig Gillespie and written by Nancy Oliver. Emily Mortimer, Paul Schneider.

programme.title: Mare of Easttown
programme.desc: Mare visits a grisly murder scene before informing the victim's enraged father. As a video from the night of the crime surfaces, Mare questions suspects in the case and gives an icy welcome to County Detective Colin Zabel, who's been called in to assist. Later, Mare bumps heads with locals and airs concerns about her grandson Drew in light of her late son's mental health struggles.

programme.title: Dreamgirls
programme.desc: Supremely entertaining adaptation of the Broadway hit about the ups and downs of a 1960s girl group. Jennifer Hudson won a Best Supporting Actress Oscar for her role.

programme.title: The Blind Side
programme.desc: This inspirational drama stars Sandra Bullock as Leigh Anne Touhy, a headstrong, wealthy Memphis woman who welcomes into her home Michael Oher, a deeply troubled African-American high-school student who turns out to be gifted at playing football.

programme.title: Man Up
programme.desc: In this delightful romantic-comedy Nancy, an unlucky-in-love thirtysomething, meets Jack, a heartbroken divorcé who has recently tried online dating and mistakes Nancy for his arranged blind date when they cross paths. Nancy plays along with the ruse, and the unlikely duo soon find themselves on a whirlwind journey neither of them expected.

programme.title: Speed 2: Cruise Control
programme.desc: Sandra Bullock returns as Annie, the spunky heroine from \"Speed,\" as she joins her new beau, Alex (Jason Patric), on an ocean liner. Unfortunately, also aboard is a madman who takes control of the ship and threatens to sink her in a plot to steal millions in jewels and seek revenge for his devastating illness. Willem Dafoe, Temuera Morrison, Brian McCardie.

programme.title: Dante's Peak
programme.desc: Pierce Brosnan stars as a volcanologist in this action-packed thriller featuring impressive special effects. Harry Dalton (Brosnan) warns a Washington town of an impending eruption, but its residents are reluctant to evacuate...until it's too late. Linda Hamilton.

programme.title: SI
programme.desc: After a baseball game, an Asian American boy navigates microaggression with his friends through seemingly innocent jokes and games.

programme.title: Grand Canyon
programme.desc: Life in Los Angeles is examined through the friendship between a lawyer who gets stranded in a bad part of town and the tow-truck driver who comes to his aid.

programme.title: The Beguiled
programme.desc: In this captivating, erotically charged Civil War drama, a deserter from the Union Army seeks refuge at an all-female boarding school in Virginia, where the ladies compete for his affections while tending to his injuries. His presence at the school slowly poisons the relationships between the various women, who eventually turn on the soldier.

programme.title: Sunshine Cleaning
programme.desc: A single mom struggling to make ends meet persuades her slacker sister to go into the crime-scene-cleanup business to make some quick cash. Amy Adams and Emily Blunt star in this quirky, well-acted dramedy from the producers of \"Little Miss Sunshine.\" Alan Arkin, Jason Spevack, Steve Zahn. Directed by Christine Jeffs.

programme.title: The Watch
programme.desc: Four suburbanites stumble upon an alien invasion while volunteering as a neighborhood-watch group, and they fight to protect their block from evil extraterrestrials in this madcap sci-fi comedy.

programme.title: Pray, Obey, Kill
programme.sub-title: Don't Be Afraid to Go Close
programme.desc: Following the trial, the sect's leader relishes her newfound celebrity and intensifies her demands on the congregation. As they question whether the court had a full picture for its verdict, Martin and Anton access never-before-seen material that contradicts the forensic evidence. Finally, the journalists speak to a person close to the case who reveals a missing piece of the puzzle.

programme.title: Primal Fear
programme.desc: Richard Gere and Oscar nominee Edward Norton star in this intense courtroom drama. Gere plays slick lawyer Martin Vail, who agrees to defend a guileless 19-year-old (Norton) who has been accused in the brutal murder of the Archbishop of Chicago. Though Vail sees the case as a way to gain publicity, the revelations in the case begin to chill him.

programme.title: A Black Lady Sketch Show
programme.sub-title: But the Tilapias Are Fine Though, Right?

programme.title: Mare of Easttown
programme.desc: Det. Mare Sheehan shoulders her chief's directive to revive an unsolved missing person's case amid increased community pressure. Later, while her loved ones celebrate her ex-husband Frank's engagement, Mare attends a celebration for her legendary high school basketball win and connects with Richard, a professor who's new in town. Series premiere.

Later, Mare bumps heads with locals and airs concerns about her grandson Drew in light of her late son's mental health struggles.

programme.title: Contraband
programme.desc: This nail-biting thriller follows smuggler Chris Farraday (Mark Wahlberg) as he faces ruthless drug lords, vicious criminals, corrupt officials and trigger-happy hit men in a bid to help his desperate brother-in-law settle a debt.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: Penance creates an amplifier to spread Mary's hope-inspiring song across the city, but first, Mary must find her elusive voice. As danger mounts against her group, Amalia propositions an unlikely ally and sets out to expand the Orphanage's reach. Swann further entangles Augie and Mundi in his business affairs.

programme.title: Reasonable Doubt
programme.desc: A hotshot district attorney contends with a killer following a deadly hit and run that ties their fates together in this white-knuckle thriller. After acquitting the accused of the crime that he himself committed, the DA finds his family in danger and his future in jeopardy.

programme.title: The Photograph
programme.desc: The estranged daughter of a famed photographer initiates a romantic relationship with an up-and-coming journalist who is working on a story about her late mother's life and artistic legacy after discovering an old photograph in a safe-deposit box.

programme.title: Lonely Blue Night
programme.desc: An awkward family reunion at a business dinner leads a Chinese mother to realize the consequences of leaving her daughter in the care of an American homestay family.

programme.title: Independence Day
programme.desc: An army of alien spaceships attack Earth and threaten to destroy the human race, but a handful of survivors band together to stop the invasion.

programme.title: Antwone Fisher
programme.desc: Denzel Washington made his directorial debut with this beautifully acted, fact-based drama. Derek Luke is sensational as Antwone Fisher, a sailor known for his violent temper tantrums. With the help of psychiatrist Jerome Davenport (Washington), Fisher comes to terms with his devastating past. The real Antwone Fisher wrote the screenplay. Joy Bryant.

programme.title: Words and Pictures
programme.desc: In this delightfully witty comedy-drama, an English teacher challenges an art teacher to a contest to determine whether words or images are more powerful. As the student body are drawn into the conflict, love blooms in the heat of battle.

programme.title: The High Note
programme.desc: The overworked, overlooked, and underappreciated personal assistant to a superstar singer seizes the opportunity to revitalize her boss's languishing career - and to realize her childhood dream of becoming a music producer. Both women discover friendship and professional fulfillment amidst Los Angeles's competitive music scene.

programme.title: Beverly Hills Cop
programme.desc: A crack Detroit detective pursues a pal's killer through the plastic jungle of Southern California, where he tweaks authority, tumbles with the bad guys and bends the rules.

programme.title: Beverly Hills Cop II
programme.desc: Eddie Murphy returns as smooth Detroit street cop Axel Foley, who's back on the West Coast to track down a gunman and investigate a series of violent robberies. John Ashton, Ronny Cox and Judge Reinhold reprise their roles.

programme.title: The Five-Year Engagement
programme.desc: A couple named Tom and Violet find their wedding plans interrupted by a number of surprises over the course of five years in this endearing romantic comedy, as Violet must move to Michigan for school and Tom is frustrated by missed job opportunities.

programme.title: A Black Lady Sketch Show
programme.sub-title: So You Just Out Here Chloroforming Anybody?

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: Penance creates an amplifier to spread Mary's hope-inspiring song across the city, but first, Mary must find her elusive voice. As danger mounts against her group, Amalia propositions an unlikely ally and sets out to expand the Orphanage's reach. Swann further entangles Augie and Mundi in his business affairs.

programme.title: The Debt
programme.desc: In this taut thriller, celebrated Mossad agent Rachel Singer must find out the truth when a man appears claiming to be the Nazi war criminal she supposedly killed 30 years earlier, during a mission that made her a legend.

programme.title: Assault on Precinct 13
programme.desc: Gritty action fires up this intense crime drama. On New Year's Eve inside a Detroit police station, an officer (Ethan Hawke) must round up a makeshift brigade of cops and criminals when the precinct is besieged by a relentless mob. The film is an effective refashioning of the 1976 film of the same name. Laurence Fishburne, Drea de Matteo, Brian Dennehy, John Leguizamo.

programme.title: The Girl With All the Gifts
programme.desc: In this engaging horror thriller set in a world overrun by zombies, a trio of soldiers, a teacher and a scientist are forced to protect a young girl whose immunity to the outbreak could be the key to saving humanity.

programme.title: Darkest Hour
programme.desc: This riveting historical drama depicts the early days of Winston Churchill's leadership of the U.K. during WWII, as he tries to rally the nation to action while many of his contemporaries advocate peace talks with Hitler.

programme.title: Blood and Wine (?)
programme.desc: A wealthy wine dealer plans a jewel heist when his money starts to run out. Bob Rafelson directed.

programme.title: Rocky IV
programme.desc: Rocky Balboa goes up against a technologically trained Soviet named Ivan Drago after his one-time nemesis, Apollo Creed, is brutally slaughtered in the boxing ring during a lopsided exhibition match against the superhuman Russian boxer.

programme.title: Speed 2: Cruise Control
programme.desc: Sandra Bullock returns as Annie, the spunky heroine from \"Speed,\" as she joins her new beau, Alex (Jason Patric), on an ocean liner. Unfortunately, also aboard is a madman who takes control of the ship and threatens to sink her in a plot to steal millions in jewels and seek revenge for his devastating illness. Willem Dafoe, Temuera Morrison, Brian McCardie.

programme.title: The Mummy Returns
programme.desc: Action and adventure erupt yet again when the evil mummy returns in this effects-laden sequel to the 1999 hit. In 1933, Rick and Evie's son Alex joins the gang to take on the resurrected Imhotep, who's battling the Scorpion King for world domination. Brendan Fraser, Arnold Vosloo, Rachel Weisz, John Hannah, Oded Fehr, Freddie Boath.

programme.title: Varsity Blues
programme.desc: In this rousing coming-of-age tale, a second-string high-school quarterback (James Van Der Beek) replaces the injured starter. At first, the quarterback revels in his new role, but then, his relaxed attitude causes problems with his gung-ho coach (Jon Voight). Paul Walker, Rob Lester, Scott Caan, Richard Lineback, Ali Larter, Tiffany C. Love.

programme.title: Our Brand Is Crisis
programme.desc: In this smart, satrical comedy, a female political consultant is hired to work on the campaign of a Bolivian presidential candidate who has fallen behind in the polls. She faces off against her rival, who is working on the opponent's campaign and is looking for every opportunity to antagonize her.

programme.title: Igby Goes Down
programme.desc: This darkly funny coming-of-age story boasts an outstanding ensemble. Igby is a rich teen who rebels against his dysfunctional family, including a yuppie brother, a tyrannical mother and a mentally ill father.

programme.title: 27 Dresses
programme.desc: Wedding mania gets a comic spin in the tale of Jane (Katherine Heigl), who's always a bridesmaid and never a bride. Jane's passion for all things nuptial is tested when she's asked to plan her sister's wedding to the man she secretly loves. A cynical columnist (James Marsden) who falls for Jane while surreptitiously writing a human-interest story about her further complicates Jane's dreams of love and marriage.

programme.title: Stand Up Guys
programme.desc: In this touching crime comedy, an aging crook is released from prison after 28 years, and he soon reunites with two friends for a new scheme that incurs the wrath of a dangerous mob boss.

programme.title: One More Time
programme.desc: In this touching drama, a musician reeling from personal and professional disappointments moves into the Hamptons home of her father, a Sinatra-esque crooner still hoping to make a career comeback. In time, father and daughter bond while seeking success in the music industry.

programme.title: Unforgettable
programme.desc: In this riveting female-centric thriller, a jilted ex-wife grows jealous of her former husband's new bride, and decides to destroy the latter's reputation in an attempt to get her old life back.

programme.title: The Good Lie
programme.desc: Sudanese refugees get a second chance at life when a humanitarian effort brings them to America.

programme.title: The Whole Truth
programme.desc: Lawyer Richard Ramsay agrees to defend the son of a close friend after he is accused of killing his wealthy, abusive father. However, Ramsay quickly realizes that the case is more complex than he initially thought in this twisty legal drama.

programme.title: The Punisher
programme.desc: The Marvel Comics superhero leaps into action in this gripping revenge thriller. When his family is slaughtered, FBI agent Frank Castle turns into a merciless fighting machine, intent on exacting brutal revenge on a crime lord and his ruthless squad of killers.

programme.title: Love and a .45
programme.desc: Saga about fugitive lovers on the run from the police and assorted criminals.

programme.title: The Recruit
programme.desc: Al Pacino and Colin Farrell star in this taut thriller from Roger Donaldson, the director of \"No Way Out\" and \"Thirteen Days.\" Pacino plays a CIA operative who recruits a computer whiz to find a mole in the agency's ranks. While studying at the agency's secret training camp, the recruit falls for a fellow student and learns that nothing is what it seems.

programme.title: The Wings of the Dove
programme.desc: A beautiful, strong-willed heiress is torn between loyalty to her family, who believes she should marry a wealthy suitor, and her love for a poor journalist. Based on the novel by Henry James. Helena Bonham Carter, Linus Roache, Alison Elliott, Charlotte Rampling, Elizabeth McGovern, Michael Gambon, Alex Jennings.

programme.title: Feast of Love
programme.desc: Bittersweet, multilayered treat features a standout performance by Morgan Freeman, who acts as a kind of all-seeing commentator who regales viewers with his observations on the relationship complications running rampant in his Oregon town awash with lovestruck romantics.

programme.title: The Others
programme.desc: Set on the Channel Islands in 1945, this atmospheric ghost story deals with a troubled young mother (Nicole Kidman) who moves her two children into a spooky mansion while awaiting the return of her long missing husband from the war. Alakina Mann. Alejandro Amenabar, whose Spanish film \"Abre los Ojos\" was remade as \"Vanilla Sky,\" wrote and directed. Christopher Eccleston, Fionnula Flanagan, James Bentley.

programme.title: In the Heart of the Sea
programme.desc: In this harrowing historical drama set in the winter of 1820, the crew of the New England whaling ship the Essex struggle to survive after an attack by a rogue sperm whale leaves them stranded at sea for 90 days.

programme.title: This Means War
programme.desc: Big laughs abound when two top CIA spies find their enduring friendship put to the ultimate test when they engage in an all-out battle to win the affections of a beautiful woman after they discover they are both dating her.

programme.title: Lucy in the Sky
programme.desc: After a life-altering expedition into deep space, Lucy Cola, an astronaut, must return to Earth and reintegrate into everyday life. However, Lucy's cosmic experiences begin to take a toll on her connection to the real world as she spirals into a mental state that her world is too small to contain.

programme.title: The Debt
programme.desc: In this taut thriller, celebrated Mossad agent Rachel Singer must find out the truth when a man appears claiming to be the Nazi war criminal she supposedly killed 30 years earlier, during a mission that made her a legend.

programme.title: Darkest Hour
programme.desc: This riveting historical drama depicts the early days of Winston Churchill's leadership of the U.K. during WWII, as he tries to rally the nation to action while many of his contemporaries advocate peace talks with Hitler.

programme.title: Unbreakable
programme.desc: Director M. Night Shyamalan followed the chilling \"The Sixth Sense\" with this riveting thriller. Bruce Willis is security guard David Dunn, who survives a devastating train wreck miraculously unharmed. The owner (Samuel L. Jackson) of a comic-book art gallery sees him as a mysterious protector with a higher calling, but Dunn is doubtful. Robin Wright Penn, Spencer Treat Clark, Eamonn Walker.

programme.title: Abraham Lincoln: Vampire Hunter
programme.desc: President Abraham Lincoln moonlights as a vampire hunter after learning that his mother was killed by bloodsuckers in this wildly fun supernatural action thriller adapted from the genre-bending novel.

programme.title: Gamer
programme.desc: Gerard Butler stars in this high-octane action spectacle as Kable, a flesh-and-blood man whose actions are controlled by popular champion gamer Simon (Logan Lerman) in a deadly first-person-shooter game called \"Slayers.\" Because the program is hugely popular, the game's unscrupulous creator (Michael C. Hall) has made a fortune from it and will do everything in his power to make sure Kable can never escape the game. Directed by Mark Neveldine and Brian Taylor.

programme.title: Punisher: War Zone
programme.desc: Ray Stevenson does a bang-up job as Frank Castle, AKA the Punisher, the tough-guy vigilante from the Marvel Comics series. In this explosive installment, he's in New York City to take on a ruthless scar-faced mob boss named Jigsaw (Dominic West). Wayne Knight is a blast as Microchip, the Punisher's weapons-supplying expert. Julie Benz, Dash Mihok, Colin Salmon, Doug Hutchison, T.J. Storm. Directed by Lexi Alexander.

programme.title: Motherless Brooklyn
programme.desc: A private detective living with Tourette's syndrome in 1950s New York City tries to solve the murder of his best friend and mentor. His case takes him through the Harlem jazz scene, the Brooklyn slums, and into the ranks of the city's most powerful men.

programme.title: Rapture-Palooza
programme.desc: In this hilariously irreverent comedy, Seattle suburbanites Ben and Lindsey learn that life after the Rapture is no picnic when the Beast himself moves into their neighborhood and aims to make lovely Lindsey his infernal bride.

programme.title: Walk the Line
programme.desc: Joaquin Phoenix and Reese Witherspoon give award-winning performances and do their own singing in this touching portrait of music legend Johnny Cash and his tumultuous love affair with June Carter. Ginnifer Goodwin, Robert Patrick, Dallas Roberts. Directed by James Mangold.

programme.title: American Woman (?)
programme.desc: Set in small-town Pennsylvania, a foxy grandmother in her early thirties struggles to make ends meet with her job as a supermarket cashier. She tries to provide for her 16-year-old daughter who's a single mom. Once her daughter disappears after a night out, the narrative spans the next 11 years as she raises her grandson, attempting to find real love and seeking answers for the mystery which may come at last.

programme.title: The Quarry
programme.desc: After killing a traveling preacher, a fugitive drifter poses as his victim and endears himself to a remote Texas town with his persuasive sermons on forgiveness. The local police chief, however, suspects that something is amiss and initiates an investigation after a body is found in the local quarry.

programme.title: John Q
programme.desc: Riveting thriller about a family man whose son needs a lifesaving heart-transplant operation. When his health-care plan doesn't cover the boy's medical procedure, he takes drastic steps to rectify the situation.

programme.title: Vice
programme.desc: Prepare for serious thrills as a cop pursues a female android that escaped from a hedonistic resort where people live out their wildest fantasies. Meanwhile, the owner of the resort dispatches a band of mercenaries to eliminate the android first.

programme.title: Stigmata
programme.desc: Patricia Arquette leaves her mark in a bloody, creepy chiller about a \"self-confessed atheist\" who \"exhibits the wounds of Christ.\" Gabriel Byrne is riveting as a Vatican priest, a debunker of miracles, sent to investigate the religious phenomenon. He arrives and in due course witnesses a couple of terrifying incidents that rock his faith.

programme.title: Twelve Monkeys (?)
programme.desc: A time traveler from 2035 goes back to 1996 to investigate how a deadly virus will spread around the world.

programme.title: Lady in the Water
programme.desc: In this mesmerizing horror fantasy, an apartment manager finds a sea nymph called a \"narf\" in the complex's swimming pool, and tries to return her to her natural habitat. However, otherworldly monsters are out to stop him.

programme.title: The Rite
programme.desc: Veteran priest Father Lucas (Anthony Hopkins) teaches incredulous seminary student Michael Kovak about performing exorcisms, and together they discover that even the Vatican isn't free from the Devil's influence in this terrifying supernatural thriller. Inspired by a true story.

programme.title: The Running Man
programme.desc: A cop in 2019 America is framed for massacring rioting civilians during a famine. After escaping from jail he tries to prove his innocence, but is captured along with an innocent civilian, and they are forced to participate in a violent game show called \"The Running Man.\".

programme.title: Hitman (?)
programme.desc: A genetically engineered assassin known as Agent 47 finds himself on the run with a hooker after he is double-crossed on a mission in Russia. Timothy Olyphant and Dougray Scott star in the explosive unrated adaptation of the popular video game. Olga Kurylenko, Robert Knepper, Ulrich Thomsen. Directed by Xavier Gens.

programme.title: Rush
programme.desc: A female rookie cop is paired with an undercover officer trying to infiltrate a drug kingpin's organization. He is forced to partake of illegal substances as part of his cover, and he's become a junkie. She follows him down this self-destructive path after they become lovers.

programme.title: Glitter
programme.desc: Pop diva Mariah Carey stars in a rags-to-riches tale similar to her own life story. In her first starring role, Carey plays Billie Frank, a woman who struggles to overcome a troubled childhood to achieve her dreams of becoming a singing star. Max Beesley, Da Brat, Tia Texada.

programme.title: Good Boys
programme.desc: One day, 12-year-old Max gets invited by the cool kids to a kissing party. Panicked because he doesn't know how to kiss, he enlists the help of two of his friends, Thor and Lucas, to help him uncover the mystery of kissing. After online research proves to be unproductive, they decide to take the drone owned by Max's father in order to spy on the neighboring teens. When the drone unexpectedly crashes, the boys are thrust into an adventure.

programme.title: Her Smell
programme.desc: A fading '90s punk rocker struggles with life after the past success of her all-female grunge band. Now playing smaller venues and competing against her own sobriety and the pressures of motherhood, she takes a hiatus from the stage, to find herself and her sober creativity.

programme.title: The Kitchen
programme.desc: When their mobster husbands are sent to prison by the FBI, three New York housewives decide to continue their husbands' business on their own, soon becoming the most powerful mobsters in 1970s Hell's Kitchen.

programme.title: Broken City
programme.desc: In this nail-biting thriller, the mayor of NYC hires a disgraced former cop, now working as a private eye, to expose his wife's infidelities. As he does so, the PI begins to unravel a mystery that could bring about the end of more than just a marriage.

programme.title: Last Knights
programme.desc: In this action-packed medieval tale, a skilled warrior and his small clan fight back against an oppressive ruler in order to avenge the murder of their master.

programme.title: Before the Devil Knows You're Dead
programme.desc: Director Sidney Lumet, at age 83, proves that he still has what it takes to enthrall an audience. This riveting crime thriller follows financially strapped brothers (Philip Seymour Hoffman, Ethan Hawke) whose foolproof jewelry-store heist goes awry in tragic ways that leave two people dead. Albert Finney is superb as the siblings' father, and owner of the targeted shop.
